Package com.eclipsesource.tabris

Interface VersionCheck

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultVersionCheck
    public interface VersionCheck

    A VersionCheck can be added by calling TabrisClientInstaller.setVersionCheck(VersionCheck). It's methods will be called before a UISession will be created. You can implement the accept(String, String) to either accept or decline the requesting client.

    Please Note: The methods of the VersionCheck are called before a UISession exists. This means you won't have access to any ClientService or other session scoped APIs.

    Since:
    1.4

    • Method Detail

      • accept

        boolean accept​(java.lang.String clientVersion,
               java.lang.String serverVersion)

        Will be called before a UISession will be created. By returning true the requesting client will be accepted and a UISession will be created. By return false the requesting client will be declined and received the error message defined in getErrorMessage(String, String).

        Parameters:
        clientVersion - the Tabris version that requesting client submits.
        serverVersion - the Tabris version of the server.

      • getErrorMessage

        java.lang.String getErrorMessage​(java.lang.String clientVersion,
                                 java.lang.String serverVersion)

        Will be called when the accept(String, String) method declines a client. The returned message will be displayed on the declined client.

        Parameters:
        clientVersion - the Tabris version that requesting client submits.
        serverVersion - the Tabris version of the server.
